# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

## Summary
Successfully implemented Vercel Web Analytics in the React + Vite application following the official Vercel documentation for React applications.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed Dependencies
- Added `@vercel/analytics` package to the project using npm
- Package version installed: Latest version from npm registry

### 2. Modified Files

#### `src/App.jsx`
- **Import Added**: Added `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react';` at the top of the file
- **Component Added**: Placed `<Analytics />` component inside the `<BrowserRouter>` component, after the `<Suspense>` wrapper
- This placement ensures analytics tracking works across all routes in the application

#### `package.json`
- Added `@vercel/analytics` to dependencies

#### `package-lock.json`
- Updated automatically by npm to include @vercel/analytics and its dependencies (227 packages)

## Implementation Details

The Analytics component was strategically placed:
- Inside `<BrowserRouter>` to enable route change tracking
- After `<Suspense>` and `<Routes>` to ensure it doesn't interfere with lazy loading
- This follows the official Vercel documentation for React applications

The implementation provides:
- Automatic page view tracking
- Route change detection with react-router-dom
- Minimal performance impact (Analytics component is lightweight)
- Privacy-compliant tracking

## Verification

✅ Build completed successfully without errors
✅ All existing tests pass (2 tests passing)
✅ No linting errors introduced
✅ Application structure preserved

## Next Steps

To complete the setup:
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Project → Analytics tab → Enable)
2. Deploy the application to Vercel
3. Verify tracking by checking browser Network tab for requests to `/_vercel/insights/view`
4. View analytics data in the Vercel dashboard after deployment

## Notes

- The Analytics component only sends data in production mode by default
- In development, it will log to console instead of sending data
- No additional configuration is needed for basic tracking
- Route support is automatically enabled with react-router-dom integration
